Mexican Stocks: America Movil, Banorte and Penoles Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-26T20:50:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/mexican-stocks-america-movil-banorte-and-penoles-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:59 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.4 percent to 34,042.22.  America Movil SAB de CV (AMXL)   rose 0.5 percent to 14.8
pesos. Latin America’s largest wireless carrier gained in line
with equity markets after Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  indicated that data aren’t pointing to a recession in
the U.S. and the economy doesn’t require immediate stimulus.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB de CV (GFNORTEO)   jumped 5.1
percent to 44.53 pesos, the largest gain since June 2010.
Mexico’s central bank kept its benchmark interest rate at a
record low today and signaled it may lower borrowing costs to
safeguard domestic growth.  Industrias Penoles SAB de CV (PE&OLES* MM) rose 2.7 percent
to 543.17 pesos. The Mexican precious metals miner advanced as
gold climbed afterBernanke offered no plan for further monetary
easing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
